<paragraph id="470936B385584F35FF36E8F7FE606632" blockId="15.[151,1437,229,448]" pageId="15" pageNumber="53">
An easily distinguishable species by the hyphae with clamp-connections and inamyloid, globose basidiospores about 
<quantity id="804E9B5685584F35FE27E91EFE076658" box="[390,481,268,294]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" metricValueMax="9.0" metricValueMin="6.0" pageId="15" pageNumber="53" unit="mm" value="7.5" valueMax="9.0" valueMin="6.0">6–9 µm</quantity>
in diam. It is reported from northern 
<collectingCountry id="3FA1762385584F35FC36E91EFBE96658" box="[919,1039,268,294]" name="Argentina" pageId="15" pageNumber="53">Argentina</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="3FA1762385584F35FBBBE91EFB836658" box="[1050,1125,268,294]" name="Brazil" pageId="15" pageNumber="53">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry id="3FA1762385584F35FB03E91EFAF06658" box="[1186,1302,268,294]" name="Colombia" pageId="15" pageNumber="53">Colombia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="23274B4285584F35FA85E91EFE9F6632" author="Hjortstam, K. &amp; Ryvarden, L." pageId="15" pageNumber="53" pagination="27 - 146" refId="ref8607" refString="Hjortstam, K. &amp; Ryvarden, L. (2007 a) Checklist of corticioid fungi (Basidiomycotina) from the tropics, subtropics, and the southern hemisphere. Synopsis Fungorum 22: 27 - 146." type="journal article" year="2007">Hjortstam &amp; Ryvarden 2007a</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
